window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>P. Djeli Clark returns to the historical fantasy universe of <i>A Dead Djinn in Cairo</i>, with the otherworldly adventure novella <i>The Haunting of Tram Car 015</i>.&nbsp;</p> <p>Cairo, 1912: The case started as a simple one for the Ministry of Alchemy, Enchantments, and Supernatural Entities - handling a possessed tram car. Soon, however, Agent Hamed Nasr and his new partner, Agent Onsi Youssef, are exposed to a new side of Cairo stirring with suffragettes, secret societies, and sentient automatons in a race against time to protect the city from an encroaching danger that crosses the line between the magical and the mundane.</p>"; 
